sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant APP as Application Layer<br/>(C binary)
    participant EXI as EXI Codec
    participant TLS as TLS Layer
    participant SRV as Server

    Note over APP,SRV: IEEE 2030.5 uses EXI (W3C) — schema-informed compact XML<br/>schema: sep.xsd  |  body: ~50–200 bytes vs. ~500–2000 bytes text XML

    APP ->> EXI: DERControl struct {mrid, interval, DERControlBase}

    EXI ->> TLS: POST /edev/{sfdi}/der/1/derst<br/>Content-Type: application/sep+xml<br/>[EXI binary body]

    TLS ->> SRV: [AES-128-CCM-8 encrypted]

    SRV -->> TLS: 200 OK / 204 No Content
    TLS -->> EXI: response body
    EXI -->> APP: decoded response struct
